          "treatment": "Treat underlying cause urgently. NaHCO3 (50-100 mEq IV) if pH <7.1-7.2 with impaired cardiac contractility or severe hyperkalemia. Not recommended for DKA or lactic acidosis (unless extreme pH). RRT if refractory (dialysis for toxins, CRRT for shock)."
